==Defeated Incumbents==
Some other seats that changed hands had new parliamentary candidates for the incumbent party

Labour:
*[[Alan Wynne Williams]]- [[Carmarthen East and Dinefwr (UK Parliament constituency)|Carmarthen East and Dinefwr]] (MP since 1987)
*[[Christine Butler]]- [[Castle Point (UK Parliament constituency)|Castle Point]] (MP since 1997)
*[[Fiona Jones]]- [[Newark (UK Parliament constituency)|Newark]] (MP since 1997)
*[[George Turner (UK politician)|George Turner]]- [[Norfolk North West (UK Parliament constituency)|Norfolk North West]] (MP since 1997)
*[[Eileen Gordon]]- [[Romford (UK Parliament constituency)|Romford]] (MP since 1997)
*[[Keith Darvill]]- [[Upminster (UK Parliament constituency)|Upminster]] (MP since 1997)
*[[David Lock]]- [[Wyre Forest (UK Parliament constituency)|Wyre Forest]] (MP since 1997)

Conservatives:

*[[Stephen Day (MP)|Stephen Day]]- [[Cheadle (UK Parliament constituency)|Cheadle]] (MP since 1987)
*[[Christopher Frazer]]- [[Mid Dorset and North Poole (UK Parliament constituency)|Mid Dorset and North Poole]] (MP since 1997)
*[[Ian Bruce]]- [[Dorset South (UK Parliament constituency)|Dorset South]] (MP since 1987)
*[[Nick St Aubyn]]- [[Guildford (UK Parliament constituency)|Guildford]] (MP since 1997)
*[[David Prior (UK politician)|David Prior]]- [[Norfolk North (UK Parliament constituency)|Norfolk North]] (MP since 1997)
*[[Patrick Nicholls]]- [[Teignbridge (UK Parliament constituency)|Teignbridge]] (MP since 1983)

Liberal Democrats:

*[[Peter Brand]]- [[Isle of Wight (UK Parliament constituency)|Isle of Wight]] (MP since 1997)
*[[Jackie Ballard]]- [[Taunton (UK Parliament constituency)|Taunton]] (MP since 1997)

Ulster Unionist:

*[[William Ross (Northern Irish politician)|Willie Ross]]- [[East Londonderry (UK Parliament constituency)|East Londonderry]] (MP since 1974)
*[[Cecil Walker]]- [[North Belfast (UK Parliament constituency)|North Belfast]] (MP since 1983)
*[[William Thompson (Ulster)|William Thompson]]- [[West Tyrone (UK Parliament constituency)|West Tyrone]] (MP since 1997)

