      <text xml:space="preserve">{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2010}}
{{Infobox musical artist  &lt;!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians --&gt;
| name            = Bing Crosby
| Img             = Bing Crosby in Road to Singapore trailer.jpg
| Img_capt        = Crosby in ''[[Road to Singapore]]'' (1940)
| Background      = solo_singer
| Birth_name      = Harry Lillis Crosby
| Alias           =
| Born            = {{birth date|1903|5|03|mf=y}}&lt;ref name=Grudens&gt;Grudens, 2002, p. 236. &quot;Bing was born on May 3, 1903. He always believed he was born on May 2, 1904.&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;br /&gt;[[Tacoma, Washington]], U.S.
| Origin          = [[Spokane, Washington]], U.S.
| Died            = {{death date and age|1977|10|14|1903|5|3|mf=y}}&lt;br /&gt;[[Madrid]], [[Spain]]
| Instrument      = Vocals
| Voice type      = [[Baritone]]/[[Bass-baritone]]
| Genre           = [[Traditional pop music|Traditional pop]], [[jazz]], [[vocal music|vocal]]&lt;ref&gt;[{{Allmusic|class=explore|id=genre/d131|pure_url=yes}} Music Genre: Vocal music].''Allmusic. Retrieved October 23, 2008.&lt;/ref&gt;
| Occupation      = [[Singer-songwriter]], [[actor]]
| Years_active    = 1926–1977
| Label           = [[Brunswick Records|Brunswick]], [[Decca Records|Decca]], [[Reprise Records|Reprise]], [[RCA|RCA Victor]], [[Verve Records|Verve]], [[United Artists]]
| Associated_acts = [[Bob Hope]], [[Dixie Lee]], [[Dean Martin]], [[Frank Sinatra]], [[Fred Astaire]], [[The Rhythm Boys]], [[Rosemary Clooney]], [[David Bowie]], [[Louis Armstrong]]
