|align=&quot;center&quot;|[[Image:Solidus-Nicephorus I and Staraucius-sb1604.jpg|80px]]||align=center|[[Staurakios]]&lt;br&gt;(Σταυράκιος)||align=&quot;center&quot;|2 October 811 –&lt;br/&gt;11 January 812||align=left|Only son of Nikephoros I, crowned co-emperor in December 803. Succeeded on his father's death, however he had been heavily wounded at Pliska and left paralyzed. He was forced to resign, and retired to a monastery where he died soon after
|-
|align=center|[[Image:Michael I (Byzantine Emperor).jpg|80px]]||align=center|[[Michael I Rangabe]]&lt;br&gt;(Μιχαήλ Α΄ Ραγκαβέ)||align=&quot;center&quot;|11 January 812 –&lt;br/&gt;11 July 813||align=left|Son-in-law of Nikephoros I, he succeeded Staurakios on his abdication. Resigned after the revolt under Leo the Armenian and retired to a monastery, where he died on 11 January 844
|-
|}

